<p>I want to show how many quantity remaining in the inventory table in a dropdown list. I can't show the remaining quantity of the inventory </p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-group"&gt;             &lt;label class="control-label col-lg-4"&gt;Material&lt;/label&gt;             &lt;div class="col-lg-8"&gt;                 &lt;asp:DropDownList ID="ddlMaterial" runat="server" class="form-control" AutoPostBack="true" onselectedindexchanged="ddlMaterial_SelectedIndexChanged" /&gt;             &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And this is the cs to get the inventory </p>  <pre><code>void GetMaterials() {     con.Open();     SqlCommand cmd = new SqlCommand();     cmd.Connection = con;     cmd.CommandText = "SELECT Products.ProductID, ProductName, Inventory.Quantity FROM Products INNER JOIN Inventory ON Inventory.ProductID = Products.ProductID";     SqlDataReader dr = cmd.ExecuteReader();     ddlMaterials.DataSource = dr;     ddlMaterials.DataTextField = "ProductName" + "Quantity";     ddlMaterials.DataValueField = "ProductID";     ddlMaterials.DataBind();     con.Close(); } </code></pre>  <p>I want to look like = grape (6), apple (4) and mango (0)</p>